The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Saturday, March 01, 2003 				 CM concerned over militancy
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Barrackpore, Feb. 28: Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee today expressed concern over growing militancy and insurgency across Bengal.																								He was speaking at the closing ceremony of the sports meet of the state police at the forces training school in Latbagan here this afternoon.																								Though insurgency is creeping in, we will definitely put a brake on it, he said. The police were told to be on alert against the Kamtapuris in the north and the Peoples War in the south. Apparently hinting at the Dhantola incident, he also urged them to check the spate in robberies.
